Unit Requirements Document: Unit 4 - Contemporary Issues & Critical Literacy
records.description: **To empower students with the critical literacy skills needed to analyze and engage with complex contemporary issues from a culturally-grounded, postcolonial perspective. This unit will connect classroom learning directly to the students' lived realities and the pressing challenges facing Aotearoa.**

records.title: Unit Requirements Document: Unit 2 - Decolonized Aotearoa History
records.description: **To create a comprehensive, evidence-based, and culturally affirming learning experience that centers Māori perspectives, agency, and resistance in the history of Aotearoa New Zealand. This unit will directly challenge colonial narratives and equip students to critically analyze the historical roots of contemporary society.**

records.title: Unit Requirements Document: Unit 7 - Digital Technologies & AI Ethics
records.description: **To provide senior students with a robust, critical, and hands-on understanding of the core principles of artificial intelligence, its ethical implications, and the skills required to interact with it effectively and safely. This unit will position our ākonga as informed digital citizens and creators.**

records.title: Unit Requirements Document: Unit 4 - Contemporary Issues & Critical Literacy
records.description: **To empower students with the critical literacy skills needed to analyze and engage with complex contemporary issues from a culturally-grounded, postcolonial perspective. This unit will connect classroom learning directly to the students' lived realities and the pressing challenges facing Aotearoa.**

records.title: Unit Requirements Document: Unit 2 - Decolonized Aotearoa History
records.description: **To create a comprehensive, evidence-based, and culturally affirming learning experience that centers Māori perspectives, agency, and resistance in the history of Aotearoa New Zealand. This unit will directly challenge colonial narratives and equip students to critically analyze the historical roots of contemporary society.**

records.title: Unit Requirements Document: Unit 7 - Digital Technologies & AI Ethics
records.description: **To provide senior students with a robust, critical, and hands-on understanding of the core principles of artificial intelligence, its ethical implications, and the skills required to interact with it effectively and safely. This unit will position our ākonga as informed digital citizens and creators.**

records.title: Unit Requirements Document: Unit 4 - Contemporary Issues & Critical Literacy
records.description: **To empower students with the critical literacy skills needed to analyze and engage with complex contemporary issues from a culturally-grounded, postcolonial perspective. This unit will connect classroom learning directly to the students' lived realities and the pressing challenges facing Aotearoa.**

records.title: Unit Requirements Documents | Te Kete Ako
records.description: Comprehensive unit planning documents for culturally-responsive curriculum design

records.title: Unit Requirements Document: Unit 2 - Decolonized Aotearoa History
records.description: **To create a comprehensive, evidence-based, and culturally affirming learning experience that centers Māori perspectives, agency, and resistance in the history of Aotearoa New Zealand. This unit will directly challenge colonial narratives and equip students to critically analyze the historical roots of contemporary society.**

records.title: Unit Requirements Document: Unit 7 - Digital Technologies & AI Ethics
records.description: **To provide senior students with a robust, critical, and hands-on understanding of the core principles of artificial intelligence, its ethical implications, and the skills required to interact with it effectively and safely. This unit will position our ākonga as informed digital citizens and creators.**
